1 Section 1. Section 39-1365.01, Revised Statutes Cumulative
2 Supplement, 2024, is amended to read:
3 39-1365.01 (1) The department shall be responsible for developing a
4 specific and long-range state highway system plan. The department shall
5 annually formulate plans to meet the state highway system needs of all
6 facets of the state and shall assign priorities for such needs. The
7 department shall, on or before December 1 of each year, present such
8 plans and the report required in section 39-1365.02 to the Legislature.
9 The plans shall be referred to the appropriate standing committees of the
10 Legislature for review.
11 (2) The department shall consider the preservation of the existing
12 state highway system asset as its primary priority except as may
13 otherwise be provided in state or federal law. In establishing secondary
14 priorities, the department shall consider a variety of factors,
15 including, but not limited to, current and projected traffic volume,
16 safety requirements, economic development needs, current and projected
17 demographic trends, and enhancement of the quality of life for all
18 Nebraska citizens. The state highway system plan shall:
19 (a) Include include the designation of those portions of the state
20 highway system which shall be expressways; and .
21 (b) Account for highway revenue raised by each district specified in
22 section 39-1102. Not less than seventy percent of revenue raised in each
23 district shall be allocated to any project within the district.
24 Sec. 2. Original section 39-1365.01, Revised Statutes Cumulative
25 Supplement, 2024, is repealed.
